choices.text:
my overactive imagination. My dad used to tell me stories before bedtime, but about ancient times. Since I’d already decided we were true psuedosapients, he realized that i needed a bedtime story to believe in, as well. So he invented a more familiar story for me to interrogate, one honest enough to capture some of the pain but also have a strong enough superhero to make sense of it all. I’m pretty sure this superhero climaxes here…

Super Thrillah – Book One: THE KILL ARREST

Chapter 1

“The olfactory coordinate suggests with some measure of certainty, our optimal vein of genesis is quite close to the surface. I recommend we….” The murmur of the computerized voice died in the face of the sudden influx of adrenaline into my system. The creature’s oval mouth was full. Its head was immense in comparison to its unimposing frame. You have to hold it together Rita, I shouted in my head to myself. This beast, not even two feet tall, is headed right at you. It sees you…

I tilted my right elbow to shield my venous system through my ornate but sharp green cufflinks. If the Kill Arrister (KA for short. Pronounced “ka”) puts its punch through my face, I’m afraid they’ll have my entire arm for a snack, setting off a vicious cycle of self cascading spasms writes another brokerage in my body wantonly away from its symbiotic source
